I just had a weird hmofa related dream.


So in this dream, I had found an old webcomic featuring a sparkledog girl with an orange, red, and green colorscheme. It was apparently published in both English and Spanish, but I only found the Spanish version. I can't speak Spanish, so I was essentially just looking at the pictures, and occasionally understanding a word or phrase I remembered from Spanish class.

The comic itself had two plots. The A-plot about this kid meeting the previously mentioned sparkledog waifur. They become friends and it shows their various childhood shenanigans together. Its sort of just little slice of life episodes showtime their lives together as they grew. Eventually getting to about when the guy is 15-16 years of age. Lots of sweet moments and silly jokes.

Meanwhile the B-plot is what can best be described as Breaking Bad, but the meth gives you superpowers. It follows these two guys baking up some form of super serum in a rotted out house in the middle of nowhere. One of them is an middle aged guy, who's clearly the brains. The other is a young guy, who just takes orders from the older guy. It shows them developing this drug over the years, testing it, and dealing with this shady businessesman over their product.

Each comic would start with the A-plot section, then move on to the B-plot segment. The artstyle would shift drastically when the plot switched. The A-plot was cartoony, and colored with what looked like colored pencil. The B-plot was a drawn as a harsh black and white pen sketch with a realistic style.

At first I thought they were separate comics, but over time I noticed common background characters and locations appearing in both. Eventually, a common plot thread appeared. The A-plot guy had powers himself. He could make things hot with his mind. His father also had powers, the ability to control light and concentrate beam that could burn things. Supposedly, the waifur had them as well, but it never shows them.
